Midterm Exam
Feb 21, 2026 11:29 AM
Just a reminder that the Midterm Review Exam will be Thursday, Feb. 26 at 1:00pm in DTC 825

Review the Lesson 7 slides for details. It will be 2 hours in length and there will be two parts:

First part is closed book and on paper. Make sure you bring a pen or pencil. This part is worth about 70% of your exam mark.
Second part will be using your Apache/Jenkins/GitLab VMs so make sure you bring your laptop and have those VMs ready.
You will need your Python repos available on your GitLab instance (point and carlot)
You will need to create a pipeline in Jenkins (with a Jenkinsfile in your repo). The stages will be defined in the exam.
This part is worth about 30% of your exam mark.
Please do not come into the exam room until you are asked to do so. The seating assignments will be posted outside the doors.

No electronic devices other than your laptop (in Part 2 only) are allowed, including headphones or earbuds. Your phone must be placed face down on the exam table.

